Approach - Make a new string, filter alnums, and add the charachters in lowercases. Reverse the 
new string and check. 
My Mistakes - Didn't knew the string functions, headerfiles.
My approach - Traverse through the string, make a string that is without the special charachters
and with no uppercase, take two loops, one starting with i and another with j and then compare ~ O(n^2)

T.C. - O(N)
S.C.- 0(N)


#include<cctype>    --- IMPORTANT for string functions - alnum, tolower etc
#include<string>
class Solution {
public:
    bool isPalindrome(string s) {
        string newStr = "";

        for(char c: s){
            if(isalnum(c)){
                newStr += tolower(c);
            }
        }

        return newStr == string(newStr.rbegin(),newStr.rend());
    }    
};
